headline: CSCO Q1 Earnings Call: AI Demand and New Partnerships Drive Strategic Shift
summary: Networking technology giant Cisco (NASDAQ:CSCO) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 11.4% year on year to $14.15 billion. Its non-GAAP EPS of $0.96 per share was 4.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Cisco Research: A Major Infrastructure Shift Is Underway. AI Could Double the Strain or Solve It
summary: Cisco (NASDAQ: CSCO), the worldwide leader in networking and security, today released a new global study revealing a major architectural shift underway across enterprise networks. As AI assistants, agents, and data-driven workloads reshape how work gets done, they're creating faster, more dynamic, more latency-sensitive, and more complex network traffic.
